</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
108 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<TEXT>
<P>
Are advertising agencies purposely scuttling their clients? An automobile 
manufacturer allows its agency to couple its car with a pig in the minds of TV 
viewers and potential customers. Another TV ad splashes pictures of sloppy 
people chomping on barbecued ribs. Not an appetizing image for the average 
viewer. I'll buy a carton of ladybugs to protect my garden from insects rather 
than purchase a product that uses magnified sounds of someone crunching an 
apple to advertise a safe pesticide. The apple growers should be sore about 
this one; it gives fruit lovers another reason for switching to raspberries. 
</P>
<P>
Margaret W. Romani, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
