<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLEO'S RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In reference to Bob Stanford's April 29 letter about the race of Cleopatra: She 
was black. 
</P>
<P>
Her father, Ptolemy XIII (Neus Dionysius), was black. He called himself "The 
New Osiris." (See "Sex &amp; Race," Vol. I, by J. A. Rodgers). You will see 
that the racial features of Ptolemy XIII are the same features as the Nubian 
pharaohs also pictured on the page. 
</P>
<P>
Also, if Bob Stanford didn't know, a lot of the ancient Greeks were Ethiopians 
or had Ethiopian blood (see "What They Never Told You in History Class," by 
Indus Khamit Kush). 
</P>
<P>
KIELA JAMAL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
