<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHERE'S GETTY? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish to protest the fiction, which the Los Angeles Times connives at, that 
the J. Paul Getty Museum is in Malibu. It is in Pacific Palisades, and 
therefore in the city of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
In the interests of truth and accuracy, to which I believe the Times is 
committed, I ask that this erroneous designation be rejected in the future. 
</P>
<P>
H. A. KELLY 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Palisades 
</P>
<P>
 Lori Starr, head of public information for the Getty, says the museum has a 
Malibu address because several hundred feet of the property facing the ocean is 
in Malibu. The much larger portion of the acreage is in the Pacific Palisades 
area of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
