<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050789-0037 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 53661 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 7, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Opinion; Part 5; Page 4; Column 5; Letters Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
85 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBSERVATORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reading Paul Grossberg's letter, I must concur with his "observations" on the 
famous observatory. 
</P>
<P>
When we moved here 17 years ago we were delighted to be living so close and 
made the trip, coming away with the same disappointment. Ten years later we 
tried again, hoping to find some improvement in the public relations of this 
facility. How can we inspire some effort to enlighten the visitors, especially 
children, on what an observatory means to astronomers and how it operates? 
</P>
<P>
MELBA WALLACK 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
