<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALESTINIANS DENOUNCE CALL FOR ATTACKS ON WESTERNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANAMA, Bahrain 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prominent Palestinians on Saturday condemned a senior Iranian official's call 
for the killing of five Westerners for every Palestinian slain in the uprising 
in the Israeli-occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
<P>
Britain and France, meanwhile, joined the United States in condemning Iranian 
Parliament Speaker Hashemi Rafsanjani's call on Friday to kill American, 
British and French citizens, hijack planes and blow up factories in retaliation 
for the killing of Palestinians by the Israeli army. 
</P>
<P>
"I have no idea why the Iranians would suddenly make statements about the 
Palestinians," said Sari Nusseibeh, a prominent Palestinian philosophy 
professor in the Israeli-occupied West Bank. "I believe they should really look 
into their own business and allow us to look after ourselves." 
</P>
<P>
Nusseibeh disassociated the Palestinian cause from Rafsanjani's statements. 
"They reflect a total alienation from the entire Palestinian situation, not 
only the Palestinian situation but also the political reality of the world." 
</P>
<P>
In London, Palestine Liberation Organization official Faisal Aweidah said 
Westerners aren't to blame for Israeli actions. 
</P>
<P>
"Every man has the right to say what he wants, but we do not approve of that 
policy, and we do not think it is conducive to the peace process that is going 
on around the world despite what Israel is doing." 
</P>
<P>
In Amman, Jordan, local PLO representative Abderrazak Yahia, who is a member of 
the organization's Executive Committee, said: "The Palestinian revolution 
embodied in the intifada is not based on terrorism but on a nonviolent 
strategy. . . . Rafsanjani's statement is a clear expression of a sick, 
terrorist mind." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ISRAEL -- REVOLTS; ISRAEL -- TERRITORIES AND POSSESSIONS; PALESTINIANS -- 
ISRAEL; WEST BANK (ISRAEL); GAZA STRIP; CASUALTIES; RAFSANJANI, HASHEMI; IRAN 
-- FOREIGN RELATIONS -- PLO; THREATS; TERRORISM -- IRAN 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
