<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER HOLDS DYING SON; THIEF GETS PURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NORWICH, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A thief stole a woman's purse from her home while she was outside holding her 
dying son who had been hit by a car, neighbor Trisha Garrod said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Alan Campling, 7, was hit by the car Friday after he ran into the street 
chasing a ball. He died of his injuries. 
</P>
<P>
While his mother was holding him, a thief crept into her home and took her 
purse, which held $33, Garrod said. 
</P>
<P>
"Whoever did this must be evil," she said. "They knew the child was badly 
injured, and Teresa was so distressed. It's enough to turn anybody's guts." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MOTHERS; CRIME VICTIMS; ROBBERIES -- ENGLAND; TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ENGLAND 
</P>
