<TEXT>
<P>
Iraqi Gen. Adnan Khairallah, defense minister for 10 years and President Saddam 
Hussein's closest confidant, was buried in a state funeral after he was killed 
in a helicopter crash in northern Iraq. In a statement broadcast by the state 
radio and television, the Iraqi leader said the pilot of the helicopter flying 
the 50-year-old general to Baghdad on Friday lost control during a sandstorm. 
One person reportedly survived the crash. Khairallah, deputy commander in chief 
of the armed forces, had been considered the second-most powerful official in 
the tight-knit clan that rules the country. He was both a cousin and 
brother-in-law to Hussein. 
