A judge in New Caledonia charged a hard-line separatist with murder in the 
killing of two senior leaders of the independence movement in the French South 
Pacific territory. Andre Tangopi was charged in the shooting deaths of 
Jean-Marie Tjibaou, leader of the Kanak Socialist National Liberation Front, 
