Photo, Maria Gonzalez, untitled, from the series "Still Lives and Orderly 
Days," 1983. From "The Photography of Invention: American Pictures of the 
1980s" (MIT Press: $39.95; 208 pp.; 94 illustrations), text by Joshua P. Smith 
and Merry A. Foresta. This book accompanies an exhibit at the National Museum 
of American Art, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, April 28-Sept. 10. 
Published in the 150th anniversary year of the invention of photography, it 
concentrates on "American photography's immediate present and future." 
