<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORNER POETRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So the Book review has finally given up on poetry altogether. Congratulations. 
Not only do you can the reviews. The next thing I know main man Eder 
offhandedly informs us that an epigram like " 'To write poetry after Auschwitz 
is barbaric' " is "a form of poetry, of course." (Book Review, April 16). And 
who finally shows up in your Poetry Corner but that longtimeman of letters 
Randy Newman. 
</P>
<P>
Excuse me, but wasn't it Pound who said good poetry should be as well-written 
as good prose? Newman is a talented songwriter, a talent of a higher order than 
most of the "poets" you print. But he's better off in the Calendar section with 
his blood relatives than lurking around in your "What's Cute This Week" Corner. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL GUISTA 
</P>
<P>
SANTA MARIA 
</P>
