</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bush Administration, anticipating that Gen. Manuel A. Noriega will try to 
rig elections in Panama, is considering additional punitive measures against 
the strongman after today's presidential balloting, U.S. officials said. The 
officials, who declined to be identified, said the options range from an effort 
to seize Noriega's assets abroad to enlisting the support of friendly 
democratic countries in a campaign to increase Panama's international 
isolation. 
</P>
