<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BARGAIN CORNER: PASSES FOR DOWN UNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here are several programs to consider for Australia. 
</P>
<P>
The Austrailpass offered by Railways of Australia is available in first or 
economy class for consecutive periods of 14, 21, 30, 60 or 90 days. 
</P>
<P>
Based on the current rate of exchange, the 14-day pass costs about $567 U.S. 
first-class and $347 for economy, with the 21-day pass going for about $711 and 
$446, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Deluxe Coachline offers a Koala Pass for 7, 10, 14, 21, 30, 60 and 90 days, 
about $185 for seven days and $238 for 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
Even better rates -- about 30% off the Koala Pass fares -- are offered on the 
Space Pass. However, this pass involves traveling on a standby basis, though 
seats can be confirmed up to four hours before departure. The Space Pass is 
issued in the same time periods as the Koala Pass, starting at $131 for seven 
days and $167 for 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
The Aussie Wanderer Pass provides discount rates for four itineraries around 
Australia. The pass can be used anywhere on the routes and for up to 12 months. 
A key restriction is that you can't repeat a place unless it's part of the 
routing. 
</P>
<P>
There are also several directional passes. For example, the 30-day Reef Pass 
covers the area between Cairns and Brisbane, which includes the Great Barrier 
Reef. You have to travel in one direction only, without backtracking. 
</P>
<P>
All of the programs are good until Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
Pioneer, another Australian motor coach, has Aussiepasses for 7, 10, 15, 21, 30 
and 60 days, starting at $176 for the seven-day pass. A Super Aussiepass 
combines accommodations with the coach passes. 
</P>
<P>
Contact travel agents or Australian Travel Service at (800) 232-2121, Extension 
840. 
</P>
<P>
Greyhound Australia has a bus pass starting at $176 for seven days. On the 15-, 
21-, 30- and 60-day passes, you can stay up to seven days at a place without 
this time counting against your pass. 
</P>
<P>
Mount Cook Line of New Zealand offers a 9-, 12-, 18-, 14-, 32- and 45-day 
Downunder Coach Pass good for travel in both New Zealand and Australia. The 
nine-day version is $221. 
</P>
<P>
Contact travel agents or Greyhound International at (800) 828-1985. JACK ADLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
