<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKE AND DEMOCRACY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It would seem that Mayor O'Connor and most of the San Diego City Council do not 
have the pulse of the people they purport to serve. 
</P>
<P>
By a 7-2 vote they decided to keep the "Save Miramar Lake" referendum from 
September's ballot. True, the development agreement with BCE has been 
rescinded, but it still leaves no protection for the hills on the north side of 
the lake. Even though over 47,000 voters signed the petition, they cannot vote 
on the issue. Doesn't speak too well of our democratic way. 
</P>
<P>
It would appear that the three members of "Gang of Five" up for reelection in 
September have a fear of being "in bed" with the developers publicly if the 
matter were put to a public vote. 
</P>
<P>
A.J. BLOWER 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
