<HEADLINE>
<P>
INNOVATIVE APPROACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an article (April 2) and subsequent letters, the merits and advantages of 
Leimert Park were generously extolled. My father, Walter Leimert, developed the 
area in the middle '20s, giving an entire block to the city. 
</P>
<P>
Leimert Park was probably the first community on the West Coast to merge under 
one project various developments . . . single-family homes, apartments and 
business. Really an innovation at the time. 
</P>
<P>
The homeowner association and building restrictions encouraged proper design, 
implemented and maintained abundant tree planting (before the city had a park 
department) and set the tone for community involvement. Illustrious architects 
were encouraged to design model homes for the middle class. Life magazine 
called Leimert Park the "City of the Future." 
</P>
<P>
As a young man in the '40s, I participated in the latter stages of the 
development. I am delighted that today Leimert Park is once again experiencing 
recognition as truly a lovely place in which to reside and shop. 
</P>
<P>
WALTER H. LEIMERT JR. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
