<HEADLINE>
<P>
VICTIM OF FREAK AUTO ACCIDENT DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 80-year-old woman, critically injured when she was struck by an unoccupied 
automobile at a Tustin bus stop, died at United Western Medical Center-Santa 
Ana on Saturday, Tustin police reported. 
</P>
<P>
The accident Thursday in the 13800 block of Red Hill Avenue near El Camino Real 
occurred after Barbara Greland, 45, of Santa Ana left her 1967 Mustang at a 
Mobile service station to get directions. The car, left idling, slipped into 
reverse and moved slowly backward, hitting Aletta Streeter, who was sitting on 
a bus bench. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin Police Officer Bryan Meder said the woman died at 2 p.m. Saturday at the 
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Meder said that the car had slipped into reverse, but how it did so is not 
known. He said the car was shifted into park when the woman got out of the 
auto. 
</P>
<P>
After the car struck the elderly woman, it continued onto Red Hill Avenue where 
it hit a northbound vehicle. No one was injured in that collision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
